draft-ietf-acme-emrtd-data-01
Automated Certificate Management Environment     Sebastian Robin Nielsen
Internet-Draft
Intended status: Standards Track
Expires: XX XXXX XXXX


  Automated Certificate Management Environment (ACME) eMRTD verification
                  draft-ietf-acme-emrtd-data-01

Abstract

   This document outlines a new eMRTD-based challenge type for the ACME
   protocol that enables a ACME client to perform automated IV
   validation of a individual's identity, by allowing upload of
   passport data or ID card data. This is performed by connecting
   a USB NFC reader (like ACR122U or ACR1552U) to the computer running
   the ACME client, and placing a passport or ID card on top of the
   reader, and then the user enters the CAN or vital data to enable
   access to the eMRTD from the NFC reader, inside ACME client.

